#---------------- Estimation Fuctions ----------------
#---------------- Estimate prediction image ----------------
#input: list of character strings from a lexicon
getPREDICTION = function(words, font = "mono"){
  
  pred = NULL
  target = NULL
  for (ii in 1:length(words)) {  
    # save a temporary image with the printed string
    png(filename = paste(getwd(),"/tmp.png",sep=''), width = 200, height = 40, 
        units = "px", pointsize = 20, bg = "white", res = 120)
    par(mar=c(0,0,0,0))
    plot(c(0,1), axes=F, main="", xlab="" ,ylab="", col="white")
    text(.95,0.42, words[ii], pos=4,  family=font, font=2)
    dev.off()
    
    #read the temporary image
    img = readImage(paste(getwd(),"/tmp.png",sep=''))
    #reduce dimensions
    img_t<-imageData(img)[,,1]
    
    #first step of prediction estimation: addition of pixel valuse
    if (ii == 1){
      target = img_t
    }
    else{target = target + img_t}
  }
  #second step: normalization
  pred = target/length(words)
  
  return(pred)
}
#---------------- Estimate oPE ----------------
#input: list of character strings, prediction image from the getPREDICTION function
getoPE = function(words, prediction, font = "mono"){
  
  vpe = NULL
  
  for (ii in 1:length(words)) {  
    
    # save a temporary image with the printed string
    png(filename = paste(getwd(),"/tmp.png",sep=''), width = 200, height = 40, 
        units = "px", pointsize = 20, bg = "white", res = 120)
    par(mar=c(0,0,0,0))
    plot(c(0,1), axes=F, main="", xlab="" ,ylab="", col="white")
    text(.95,0.42, words[ii], pos=4,  family=font, font=2)
    dev.off()
    
    #read the temporary image
    img = readImage(paste(getwd(),"/tmp.png",sep=''))
    #reduce dimensions
    img_t<-imageData(img)[,,1]
    
    #prediction error image estimation
    target = abs(img_t-prediction)
    #summed prediction error 
    vpe[ii] = sum(target)
  } 
  return(vpe)
}
#---------------- Estimate number of pixels ----------------
#input: list of character strings
getNPIX = function(words, font = "mono"){
  
  lum = NULL
  for (ii in 1:length(words)) {  
    
    # save a temporary image with the printed string
    png(filename = paste(getwd(),"/tmp.png",sep=''), width = 200, height = 40, 
        units = "px", pointsize = 20, bg = "white", res = 120)
    par(mar=c(0,0,0,0))
    plot(c(0,1), axes=F, main="", xlab="" ,ylab="", col="white")
    text(.95,0.42, words[ii], pos=4,  family=font, font=2)
    dev.off()
    
    #read the temporary image
    img = readImage(paste(getwd(),"/tmp.png",sep=''))
    #reduce dimensions
    img_t<-imageData(img)[,,1]
    
    #invert image values
    target = abs(img_t*-1+1)
    #sum the non-white pixels, note gray will be counted partely depending on thier gray values
    lum[ii] = sum(target)
  } 
  return(lum)
}
